  "prompt": "I have sodium bicarbonate, how can I know if is it true?",
  "response": "To verify if a substance is sodium bicarbonate (baking soda), you can perform a few simple tests:\n\n1. Visual inspection:\n- White, fine powder\n- No strong odor\n- Looks like a fine, uniform powder\n\n2. Simple tests:\n- Dissolve in water: It should dissolve completely\n- Taste: Mild, slightly alkaline taste\n- Reaction with vinegar: When mixed with vinegar, it should fizz and produce carbon dioxide bubbles\n\n3. More advanced tests:\n- pH test: Should be slightly alkaline (around 8.3)\n- Flame test: Will not produce a colored flame\n- Chemistry tests like litmus paper or professional lab analysis\n\n4. Check packaging:\n- Look for labeling indicating \"sodium bicarbonate\" or \"baking soda\"\n- Check expiration date\n- Verify manufacturer information\n\n5. Purchase from reliable sources:\n- Reputable stores\n- Pharmacy\n- Grocery stores\n- Online retailers with good reviews\n\nIf you're unsure about its purity or origin, it's best to purchase a new package from a trusted source.",
